<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" />
<title>ParkerPixiePaws — The Stitchbook (Alternating Layout)</title>
<meta name="description" content="An alternating, mobile-friendly storybook of ParkerPixiePaws amigurumi — image on one side, story on the other. Healing through stitches." />
<link rel="icon" href="/CapyGoldIcon.png" />
<style>
  :root{
    --bg:#0f0b14;         /* deep cosmos */
    --ink:#f6f1ff;        /* soft lilac-white */
    --muted:#c9bfe6;
    --gold:#D8AA3B;       /* Parker gold */
    --panel:#1a1424;      /* card bg */
    --glass:rgba(255,255,255,.06);
    --border:rgba(255,255,255,.12);
    --shadow:0 14px 40px rgba(0,0,0,.35);
    --maxw: 1100px;
  }

  *{box-sizing:border-box}
  html,body{height:100%}
  body{
    margin:0; color:var(--ink);
    background:
      radial-gradient(1200px 800px at 20% -10%, #1b1530 0%, transparent 60%),
      radial-gradient(1000px 700px at 80% 110%, #24183a 0%, transparent 60%),
      var(--bg);
    font-family: ui-rounded,"SF Pro Rounded",Quicksand,Avenir,system-ui,-apple-system,Segoe UI,Roboto,"Helvetica Neue",Arial,sans-serif;
    line-height:1.55;
  }

  /* Header / cover */
  .cover{
    padding: clamp(16px,3vw,32px);
    display:grid; place-items:center; text-align:center;
  }
  .brand{ font-weight:900; letter-spacing:.6px; font-size: clamp(22px,4.2vw,44px) }
  .tag{ color:var(--muted); font-size: clamp(14px,2vw,18px); max-width:60ch }

  /* Section rows */
  section.entry{
    padding: clamp(18px,4vw,48px) clamp(16px,3vw,32px);
    display:flex; justify-content:center;
  }
  .row{
    width:100%; max-width:var(--maxw);
    display:grid; grid-template-columns: 1.05fr 1fr; gap: clamp(16px,3vw,40px);
    align-items:center;
  }
  /* Alternate sides: even rows reverse columns on desktop */
  .row.reverse{ grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.05fr; }
  @media (max-width: 860px){
    .row, .row.reverse{ grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  /* Media (image) */
  .media{
    background: linear-gradient(180deg,var(--glass),transparent);
    border:1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius:22px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    padding: clamp(8px,1.5vw,12px);
    display:grid; place-items:center;
  }
  .media img{
    max-width:100%;
    max-height:70svh;
    height:auto; width:auto; /* natural size; no cropping */
    object-fit: contain;      /* safe if width/height ever set */
    border-radius:16px;
    border:1px solid var(--border);
    box-shadow: 0 10px 26px rgba(0,0,0,.28);
    display:block;
  }

  /* Copy panel */
  .copy{
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,.06), rgba(0,0,0,.15));
    border:1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius:22px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    padding: clamp(16px,2.6vw,28px);
  }
  .kicker{
    color:var(--gold); font-weight:800; letter-spacing:.3px;
    text-transform:uppercase; font-size:.9rem; margin:0 0 4px 0;
  }
  h2{
    margin:.1rem 0 .8rem 0; font-size:clamp(20px,2.6vw,30px);
    font-weight:900; letter-spacing:.2px;
  }
  p{ margin:.6rem 0 }
  em{ color:#eadaff; font-style:italic }
  .caption{
    margin-top:.8rem; padding-top:.6rem; border-top:1px dashed var(--border);
    color:var(--muted); font-size:.95rem;
  }

  /* Divider thread */
  .thread{
    width:100%; max-width:var(--maxw);
    height:40px; margin: 4px auto 0;
    background:
      radial-gradient(6px 6px at 20% 50%, var(--gold) 35%, transparent 36%),
      repeating-linear-gradient(90deg, transparent 0 28px, rgba(216,170,59,.35) 28px 32px, transparent 32px 64px);
    opacity:.35; filter: blur(.3px);
  }

  /* Outro */
  .outro{
    padding: clamp(24px,4vw,56px);
    display:grid; place-items:center; text-align:center;
  }
  .cta{
    margin-top:10px; display:inline-block; padding:10px 16px;
    border-radius:999px; color:var(--ink); text-decoration:none; font-weight:800;
    background:linear-gradient(180deg, var(--glass), transparent);
    border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.35);
  }
  .cta:hover{ border-color:#fff }

  /* Reveal animation */
  .reveal-up{ opacity:0; transform: translateY(18px); transition: opacity .6s ease, transform .6s cubic-bezier(.2,.8,.2,1) }
  .reveal-up.on{ opacity:1; transform: translateY(0) }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce){
    .reveal-up{ opacity:1; transform:none; transition:none }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- Cover -->
<header class="cover">
  <h1 class="brand">The Stitchbook of ParkerPixiePaws</h1>
  <p class="tag">An alternating, scrollable gallery—each friend on one side, their story on the other. Cozy, clean, and easy to read on mobile.</p>
</header>

<!-- AURORA (image left, text right) -->
<section class="entry" id="aurora">
  <div class="row">
    <figure class="media reveal-up">
      <img src="/img/Aurora.jpg" alt="Aurora the puffin amigurumi" />
    </figure>
    <article class="copy reveal-up">
      <div class="kicker">Puffin · Legacy & Light</div>
      <h2>Aurora: Legacy & Light</h2>
      <p>Aurora is for my dearest friend of thirty years — mentor, guide, mother figure. She’s always seen my strength before I did, always lit the path. Puffins are her bird: resilient travelers who thrive in harsh landscapes. Aurora is both tribute and thank-you.</p>
      <div class="caption">
        <p><em>Aurora the puffin amigurumi.</em></p>
        <p><em>Aurora the puffin — stitched in gratitude for three decades of guidance and light.</em></p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
<div class="thread" aria-hidden="true"></div>

<!-- BEJEWELED (text left, image right) -->
<section class="entry" id="bejeweled">
  <div class="row reverse">
    <article class="copy reveal-up">
      <div class="kicker">Peacock · Shimmer & Becoming</div>
      <h2>Bejeweled: Shimmer & Becoming</h2>
      <p>And then there’s Bejeweled. My peacock. My queen. My declaration. For years, I wore the mask of “everything is perfect” while I broke inside. Bejeweled is me, unmasked. She is feathers spread wide, shimmer unapologetic. She’s the reminder that the little girl inside me has finally arrived — radiant, worthy, seen.</p>
      <div class="caption">
        <p><em>Bejeweled the peacock amigurumi.</em></p>
        <p><em>Bejeweled — the moment of becoming, stitched in unapologetic shimmer.</em></p>
      </div>
    </article>
    <figure class="media reveal-up">
      <img src="/img/Bejeweled.jpg" alt="Bejeweled the peacock amigurumi" />
    </figure>
  </div>
</section>
<div class="thread" aria-hidden="true"></div>

<!-- BONNIE (image left, text right) -->
<section class="entry" id="bonnie">
  <div class="row">
    <figure class="media reveal-up">
      <img src="/img/Bonnie.jpg" alt="Bonnie the chicken amigurumi" />
    </figure>
    <article class="copy reveal-up">
      <div class="kicker">Chicken · Humor & Resilience</div>
      <h2>Bonnie: Humor & Resilience</h2>
      <p>Bonnie has the wildest origin story of them all. She was supposed to be my “Trojan chicken.” The plan was dark and raw: crochet a chicken beautiful enough for my mother to proudly display, then fill it with slips of paper — my hurts, my rage, my childhood wounds. I was going to hand it to her, let her cut it open, and finally see all I’d carried. My counselor gently suggested there might be better ways to heal from childhood PTSD.</p>
      <p>So Bonnie transformed. She became something else, someone else’s. Instead of being a Trojan horse for pain, she became a tribute for a friend whose honesty, humor, and grounding presence has been a lifeline in my recovery. This “chicken lady” fills her home with warmth and resilience, and she’s far more worthy of such a gift than my mother ever was. Bonnie isn’t trauma anymore — she’s testimony.</p>
      <div class="caption">
        <p><em>Bonnie the chicken amigurumi.</em></p>
        <p><em>Bonnie the chicken — once a Trojan plan, now a tribute to honest friendship.</em></p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
<div class="thread" aria-hidden="true"></div>

<!-- GILLIGAN (text left, image right) -->
<section class="entry" id="gilligan">
  <div class="row reverse">
    <article class="copy reveal-up">
      <div class="kicker">Pelican · Gratitude & Memories</div>
      <h2>Gilligan: Gratitude & Memories</h2>
      <p>Gilligan is a pelican for my mother-in-law, who became my family when my own mother couldn’t. He carries with him years of Florida beaches, dolphins, and seabird sightings — stitched memories of vacations and love. Gilligan isn’t just a bird; he’s a bond.</p>
      <div class="caption">
        <p><em>Gilligan the pelican amigurumi.</em></p>
        <p><em>Gilligan the pelican — sun, salt, and family stitched into a companion.</em></p>
      </div>
    </article>
    <figure class="media reveal-up">
      <img src="/img/Gilligan.jpg" alt="Gilligan the pelican amigurumi" />
    </figure>
  </div>
</section>
<div class="thread" aria-hidden="true"></div>

<!-- JADE (image left, text right) -->
<section class="entry" id="jade">
  <div class="row">
    <figure class="media reveal-up">
      <img src="/img/Jade.jpg" alt="Jade succulent planter amigurumi" />
    </figure>
    <article class="copy reveal-up">
      <div class="kicker">Succulent Planter · Steadfast & Patience</div>
      <h2>Jade: Steadfast & Patience</h2>
      <p>Jade is a planter for my husband, whose love is steady even when my energy is chaos. He’s the soil to my swirl, the anchor that lets me grow wild. Succulents bloom in unlikely places — so does love, so does resilience. Jade is a reminder of that.</p>
      <div class="caption">
        <p><em>Jade succulent planter amigurumi.</em></p>
        <p><em>Jade — a stitched planter for the anchor who lets me grow wild.</em></p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Outro -->
<footer class="outro">
  <p class="tag">If one of these speaks to you, I take limited commissions.</p>
  <a class="cta" href="/parkerpixiepaws/request/">Inquire about a custom</a>
</footer>

<script>
  // Reveal-in on scroll
  const io=new IntersectionObserver((entries)=>{
    entries.forEach(e=>{
      if(e.isIntersecting){ e.target.classList.add('on'); }
    });
  },{threshold:.2});
  document.querySelectorAll('.reveal-up').forEach(el=>io.observe(el));
</script>
</body>
</html>
